# Theory Foundation
# Andalusian cadence: iv - bIII - bII - I
# Stepwise descending bass over Phrygian harmony
# The bII -> I resolution is a zone-crossing half-step
# Each cadence ends on a major I chord (Phrygian Dominant flavor)

# Zone-Tritone Connection
# Every bII -> I resolution crosses zones
# The I chord contains a tritone (3rd & b7) pointing to its parent minor
# Cycling by 4ths mirrors the dominant cycle in jazz
# This connects the Andalusian cadence to circle-of-fifths theory

# Cycle Order (by 4ths)
# Resolves to: E -> A -> D -> G -> C -> F -> Bb -> Eb -> Ab -> Db -> F# -> B

